labels.label:
Initializes the date from which the pipeline should begin pulling data. This is part of the "Control Flow" loop to pull historical data, but is not a necessary attribute for daily/monthly data pulls when the pipeline is up to date.
There could be a separate processor group with the control flow logic removed that runs to pull current data once the historical data is done processing.
Split each station into an individual flow file.
Currently set to run once per day. Since these are predictions and they appear to be made once per month, this processor could also potentially run once per month.

Control Flow
These processors loop through each day beginning with the initial date programmed "currDate" attribute. This is only required for pulling the historical data which begins on 20230101. It is stateless, so it will not remember the last date pulled if there is an interruption in the pipeline.
